visualization:
- easy to analyse data

without visualization:
- manual scan
- time
- very difficult for large datasets

- conversion of boring data (numbers,text,etc.) into colourful graphs, charts, bars etc.

uses:
- data science
- business/marketing
- healthcare
- finance
- education
- govt./policy

- picture speaks louder than numbers

libraries for data visualization:
- matplotlib
- seaborn
- plotly
- pandas(plot)
- bokeh

advantages:
- saves time
- easy communication
- spot trends and patterns
- better decision making
- handles big data well

points to remember:
- images 60,000 times better understood than tech
- may lie if you have done any mistakes
- color choosing is important
- 90% big data fails due to lack of visualization
- Miller's law - your brain can hold 7 pieces of info. at once

- line graph: find trend/pattern
- custom graphics

- bar chart: category comparison, data analysis
- pie chart: proportion illustration, whole representation
- histogram: numerical distribution, data insights
- scatter plot: relationship between x and y